    <p>
        Having worked in the field of Refrigeration and Air Conditioning for the previous 20 years John
        started his career in education 2001 as a third level lecturer, specializing in Refrigeration and
        Air Conditioning. In addition he has provided training to the pharmaceutical, medical devices,
        telecommunications, electronics and food processing industries among others. He worked
        closely with the Department of the Environment on the introduction of FGas Regulations to
        Ireland and was deeply involved in the setting of the Irish standards for F Gas training.
    </p>
    <p>
        For the past four years he has been working as a lecturer at T.T.C. a
        third level college in Riyadh, Saudi Arabia. Among other things this is where,
        in conjunction with Rob Howe, he developed a context based learning for engineering program.
    </p>
    <p>
        John has now returned to Ireland having successfully completed his contract in K.S.A.
    </p>
