    <p>
        Brian has worked in the field of Careers Guidance for over thirty years partly in the UK
        (where he was Head of Careers Guidance at Bristol University) and partly on a wide variety
        of international projects relating to effective job search. He liaised extensively with a
        very wide range of international employers from large multinationals to small and medium
        sized employers in order to enable them to offer a wide range of careers support to their
        employees. He has developed a wide range of courses ranging from support for employees facing
        redundancy, enhancing skills of employees, effective communication, fair and effective recruitment
        as well as a tailor made range of courses for specific employers. These have been delivered on an
        international basis. His work style is highly interactive with participants being encouraged to
        contribute as much as possible and build on their own experiences to both develop skills and find the
        best route forward in relation to their career.
    </p>
